summaries.short: An enraged Lucas decides to go after Kai; Carrie reconnects with Gordon under trying circumstances.
summaries.full: An enraged Lucas looks for some trees to shake in an effort to bring down Proctor. After rattling the regulars and strippers at the Savoy, Lucas and his deputies rough up Sharp, a junkyard skinhead, for info on a Proctor-run ecstasy operation. A family crisis brings Carrie, Deva and Gordon together; Alex faces a vote of no-confidence at the tribal council.

summaries.short: Lucas busts Proctor; Emmett is tested by Sharp and his skinheads; Carrie makes progress with Gordon.
summaries.full: An illegal search warrant helps Lucas bust Proctor, at a cost. Sharp and his skinheads look for payback against Emmett, testing the limits of the deputy's patience. Carrie provides the cash for Max's treatments and takes a small step towards thawing out her relationship with Gordon and Deva. Job finally gets a lead on Rabbit.

summaries.short: Jason's past catches up to him, and Lucas; Kai teaches Rebecca a hard lesson in allegiance.
summaries.full: When Jason's past catches up to him, Lucas decides to make a deal in order to save the boy's life, and maybe his own. In the absence of Carrie, Gordon and Deva's lives spin out of control. Proctor teaches Rebecca a hard lesson in allegiance.

summaries.short: Job's close encounter with a NYC priest brings Lucas and Carrie a step closer to Rabbit.
summaries.full: In New York, Job drops in on a priest with ties to Rabbit, taking a hit for his troubles. Carrie's relationship with Gordon faces a new test. Burton silences one traitor, but another eludes him. Alex vows to deliver evidence to keep Proctor behind bars. Emmett moves on while Brock looks to move up. Lucas and Carrie brace for an epic showdown.

summaries.short: Lucas and Carrie make a detour; Agent Racine reveals the origins of his personal vendetta against Rabbit.
summaries.full: Lucas considers moving on after he and Carrie take a detour on their drive back to Banshee. Agent Racine recalls the botched case against Rabbit that has haunted him for years.

summaries.short: Season Two Finale. Fueled by painful memories, Lucas and Carrie steel themselves for a do-or-die showdown with Rabbit.
summaries.full: Season Two Finale. Fueled by the painful memories that led them to this point of no return, Lucas and Carrie steel themselves for the fight of their lives, against a vengeful Rabbit and his ruthless soldiers. In Banshee, Rebecca proves her allegiance as Proctor returns home.

summaries.short: Lucas follows up on a lead in the Cleary murder; Proctor offers Alex a peace offering.
summaries.full: Following a lead from Brock, Lucas visits a strict Amish schoolteacher who might have insights into the murder of Kinaho tribe member Lana Cleary--and the disappearance of Solomon Bowman. Emmett and Siobhan find transferring a captive Chayton more difficult than expected. Rebecca copes with the pain of her parents' rejection. Proctor offers Alex a peace offering.
